Getting Started

When you begin to share data for the first time, the computer with the most authoritative copy must be the first to send/receive, and all other computers must have the project removed from that computer before proceeding.

If your project is spread across two or more computers, and neither contains a more complete or up-to-date work, it is recommended to merge the databases into one project before sharing the project. If you need help with this process, please contact FLEx_Errors@sil.org for advice.

All other computers/users in the project will receive this project through the command "Get Project from Colleague". After that, they can continue to work on the new shared project.

For step-by-step instructions on project sharing, please search for "Get started with Send/Receive" in the Helps or click the Help button below.

Best Practices

When working, it is recommended for each user to complete a send/receive before starting the days work (to receive the most current data) and when ending the days work (to share your new changes with other users). Users who work at the same time, or who are making major changes to the database are encouraged to send/receive more often to prevent conflicts.

    As with any Send/Receive process, there are recommendations about which areas to avoid editing at the same time:

  • If you will be doing a Bulk Edit, please do a Send/Receive immediately before and after, and ask other teammates to refrain from working while you do this.
  • Try to avoid having two users work on the same interlinear text during the same send/receive cycle. This includes the Text Chart.
  • If two users adjust lexical relations in the same entry in the same Send/Receive cycle, the results may not be what you expect.

Gutangira

Igihe utangiye gusangira n'abandi amakuru ku nshuro ya mbere, mudasobwa ibite ikopi ishingirwaho igomba kuba iya mbere mu kohereza/kwakira, naho izindi mudasobwa zigomba kuba umushinga wakuwemo mbere yo gukomeza.

Iyo umushinga wawe ukwirakwiye kuri abiri cyangwa menshi mu mamashini, kandi nta nimwe ifite umurimo ukoze ku buryo bwuzuye cyangwa buhujwe n'igihe, turakugira inama yo guhuriza hamwe imbikamakuru zose mu mushinga umwe mbere yo gusangira n'abandi umushinga. Niba ukeneye ubwunganizi mu gukora ibi, wareba FLEx_Errors@sil.org kugira ngo uhabwe inama.

Izindi mudasobwa/abakoresha bose kuri uyu mushinga bazabona uyu mushinga hakoreshejwe komande "Akira umushinga uvuye kuri bagenzibawe". Nyuma y'ibyo, bashobora gukomeza gukora ku mushingwa basangijweho.

Ku bijyanye n'amabwiriza yo gusangira n'abandi umushinga itambe ku ntambwe, turagusaba gushaka "Gutangirira kuri Kohereza/Kwakira" muri Nkunganire cyangwa ugakanda kuri buto ya Nkunganire iri hasi.

Ibikorwa ntangarugero

Mu gihe ukora, buri mukoresha asabwa kurangiza kohereza/kwakira mbere yo gutangira umurimo w'umunsi (kwakira amakuru akiri mashyashya) and when ending the days work (to share your new changes with other users). Abakora ku mushinga mu gihe kimwe, cyangwa abakora impinduka zigaragara ku mbikamakuru basabwa kohereza/kwakira kenshi mu rwego rwo kwirinda amakimbirane y'ibyo bashyiramo.

    As with any Send/Receive process, there are recommendations about which areas to avoid editing at the same time:

  • If you will be doing a Bulk Edit, please do a Send/Receive immediately before and after, and ask other teammates to refrain from working while you do this.
  • Try to avoid having two users work on the same interlinear text during the same send/receive cycle. This includes the Text Chart.
  • If two users adjust lexical relations in the same entry in the same Send/Receive cycle, the results may not be what you expect.
